<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="494" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1930,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1930,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Peristomial lip constricted into a projecting tube protruding outwards from apical end of cell (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,181,1491]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[183,1404,181,1491]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Specimens of Epistylis sp.1 attached to Terebella sp. (A–C) SEM images, (D, E) light microscopy images. (A). Epistylis sp.1. on the dorsal surface of the anterior end of the worm; (B). Epistylis sp.1 on the ventral surface of the anterior end of the worm; (C). Epistylis sp.1, on grooves between neuropodia; (D–E). Epistylis sp.1 attached to buccal tentacles of Terebella sp. White arrow points to folds of the posterior region of zooid, yellow arrow points to projecting tube formed by constriction of the peristomial lip, red arrow points to macronucleus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5726367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5726367/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Figs 2D, E</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[182,218,1966,1992]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[212,1376,597,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-165@5.[212,1376,597,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Specimens of Epistylis sp.2 on Namalycastis abiuma. (A). Entire worm, dorsal view; (B). Colony of Epistylis sp.2 on parapodial dorsal cirrus; (C). Solitary Epistylis sp.2 on parapodial dorsal cirrus; (D). Premature juvenile Epistylis sp. 2, on parapodial ventral cirrus; most specimens measured along longitudinal axis. White arrow points to folds of the posterior region of zooid; yellow arrow points to projecting tube formed by constriction of the peristomial lip, red arrow points to macronucleus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5726371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5726371/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">3C</figureCitation>
). Elongate macronucleus oriented longitudinally to main axis of cell (
<figureCitation box="[988,1110,1966,1992]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,181,1491]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[183,1404,181,1491]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Specimens of Epistylis sp.1 attached to Terebella sp. (A–C) SEM images, (D, E) light microscopy images. (A). Epistylis sp.1. on the dorsal surface of the anterior end of the worm; (B). Epistylis sp.1 on the ventral surface of the anterior end of the worm; (C). Epistylis sp.1, on grooves between neuropodia; (D–E). Epistylis sp.1 attached to buccal tentacles of Terebella sp. White arrow points to folds of the posterior region of zooid, yellow arrow points to projecting tube formed by constriction of the peristomial lip, red arrow points to macronucleus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5726367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5726367/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Figs 2D, E</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1121,1157,1966,1992]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[212,1376,597,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-165@5.[212,1376,597,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Specimens of Epistylis sp.2 on Namalycastis abiuma. (A). Entire worm, dorsal view; (B). Colony of Epistylis sp.2 on parapodial dorsal cirrus; (C). Solitary Epistylis sp.2 on parapodial dorsal cirrus; (D). Premature juvenile Epistylis sp. 2, on parapodial ventral cirrus; most specimens measured along longitudinal axis. White arrow points to folds of the posterior region of zooid; yellow arrow points to projecting tube formed by constriction of the peristomial lip, red arrow points to macronucleus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5726371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5726371/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">3C</figureCitation>
). Contracted zooid ovoid in shape, with conspicuous folds posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[659,753,2002,2028]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1514,1538]" captionTargetBox="[183,1404,181,1491]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[183,1404,181,1491]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Specimens of Epistylis sp.1 attached to Terebella sp. (A–C) SEM images, (D, E) light microscopy images. (A). Epistylis sp.1. on the dorsal surface of the anterior end of the worm; (B). Epistylis sp.1 on the ventral surface of the anterior end of the worm; (C). Epistylis sp.1, on grooves between neuropodia; (D–E). Epistylis sp.1 attached to buccal tentacles of Terebella sp. White arrow points to folds of the posterior region of zooid, yellow arrow points to projecting tube formed by constriction of the peristomial lip, red arrow points to macronucleus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5726367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5726367/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">Figs 2D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[765,798,2002,2028]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox="[212,1376,597,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-165@5.[212,1376,597,1851]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Specimens of Epistylis sp.2 on Namalycastis abiuma. (A). Entire worm, dorsal view; (B). Colony of Epistylis sp.2 on parapodial dorsal cirrus; (C). Solitary Epistylis sp.2 on parapodial dorsal cirrus; (D). Premature juvenile Epistylis sp. 2, on parapodial ventral cirrus; most specimens measured along longitudinal axis. White arrow points to folds of the posterior region of zooid; yellow arrow points to projecting tube formed by constriction of the peristomial lip, red arrow points to macronucleus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5726371" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5726371/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="494">3C</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Corliss, J. O." box="[821,969,2002,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" refId="ref5456" refString="Corliss, J. O. (1979) The Ciliated Protozoa: Characterization, Classification and Guide to the Literature. 2 nd Edition. Pergamon Press, New York, New York, 455 pp." type="book" year="1979">Corliss 1979</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lynn, D. H. &amp; Small, E. B." box="[980,1207,2002,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="494" pagination="371 - 656" refId="ref8051" refString="Lynn, D. H. &amp; Small, E. B. (2002) Phylum Ciliophora Doflein, 1901. In: Lee, J. J., Leedale, G. F. &amp; Bradbury, P. (Eds.), An Illustrated Guide to the Protozoa. Organisms Traditionally Referred to as Protozoa, or Newly Discovered Groups. 2 nd Edition. Society of Protozoologists, Lawrence, pp. 371 - 656." type="book chapter" year="2002">Lynn &amp; Small 2002</bibRefCitation>
